cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper presents an algorithm for learning compact representations of data, specifically images, using a vector quantization effect. This involves adapting the sequential generation scheme of DRAW to discrete latent variables. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions generating realistic samples from datasets, which suggests a focus on generative models, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image compression, which could also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
